text.tspan: Generic chart title to silence errors
Hypothetical global meat demand if everyone in the world ate the same quantity as the average citizen of a given
country, e.g. data for the USA in 1990 hypothesises global meat demand if everyone in the world consumed the
same amount of meat as the average US citizen in 1990. Actual global meat production in 2013 was 310 million
Source: Our World in Data based on the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations
